  "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
  "body": "I find myself typing this all the time (sadly, not with Pokemon):\n\n``` javascript\nvar Pokemon = React.createClass({\n    propTypes: {\n        type: React.PropTypes.oneOf(['normal', 'fire', 'water', 'bird', '...'])\n    },\n\n    getDefaultProps: function() {\n        return {\n            type: 'normal'\n    }\n});\n```\n\nI really like how `propTypes` frame the data schema for a component. What if it could skip a step with something like:\n\n``` javascript\nvar Pokemon = React.createClass({\n    propTypes: {\n        type: React.PropTypes.oneOf(['normal', 'fire', 'water', 'bird', '...'], 'normal')\n    }\n});\n```\n",
